The paper proposes a method for hierarchical reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of reinforcement learning (RL) and machine learning (ML). The paper focuses on learning a latent variable of a hierarchical policy using mutual information maximization, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning and generative models. The paper also introduces advantage-weighted importance sampling, which is a technique used in RL. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
